arch:property.oc:show_val: A small unit consisting of fragmented bones from both sheep and cattle sized animals. There is very little evidence of burning or digestion. Most of the diagnostic bone was the remains of caprines including an astragalus of a juvenile animal. One piece of worked bone was a rib that had been ground flat on one side and very highly polished on the other. {Another piece of this, separated by a modern break, was found in the flotation from unit 6112. It has been glued together and recorded here. I hope they are adjacent units. -NR 2001} No 4mm flotation sample. Last number = 65

arch:string.div: The unique identifier for each contextual unit, matching those used in the central Çatalhöyük excavation database and in publications. The excavation uses single-context recording.
